   <mods:abstract>Lincoln already informed John Jay that troops under Colonel Campbell
            progressed upland as far as Augusta, and were preparing to cross the Savannah river when
            they suddenly retreated between 13 and 14 February. On the 18 they recrossed Briar Creek
            and burned the bridge. It is important that the friendliness of the Indians be
            maintained. Governor Rutledge has ordered 1200 of the militia and part of General
            Williamson's brigade to the upper part of the country. Lincoln hopes they will make up
            for the departure of the North Carolina troops on 10 April. The Governor has promised to
            put them under the continental articles of war if their usefulness is insufficient when
            under his command.</mods:abstract>
